modules.description: Processes RDF triples using a graph-based structure, enabling efficient querying and traversal of semantic data. It supports operations such as adding, removing, and matching triples, along with path-based navigation through graph relationships. This is used to build knowledge graphs and perform semantic reasoning in data integration tasks.

Provides a framework for constructing and manipulating RDF graphs through node-based operations. Includes core data structures for representing triples, nodes, and graphs, along with methods for graph assembly and traversal. Users can create, combine, and query RDF data using defined node relationships. Example tasks include building a graph from labeled nodes and extracting triples for semantic analysis.
